In this press briefing, President Trump discusses his expectations for China to take a more active role in dealing with North Korea. He also mentions that he hasn't discussed the possibility of military action in Syria with members of Congress. Trump expresses satisfaction with his staff's performance and believes his administration has had a successful 13 weeks. He plans to discuss trade, North Korea, and other issues with the Chinese president. Trump states that the nuclear option won't impact his choice of nominees for Senate approval. He comments on Devin Nunes recusing himself and believes he is a good person. Trump condemns the actions of Syrian President Assad and suggests that something should happen to address the situation. He mentions the possibility of discussing the issue with Russian President Putin in the future.